These are my thoughts on the situation:

I see both sides of what's being said here. The subnet is responsible for not only developing functionality in the background, but having a presence in the foreground (this includes an active social media/advertising presence, which I don't see a lot of). Additionally, communicating with the miners/Discord community is very important. These are the people who are providing support for the subnet and are directly correlated to its success. By communicating with them, it boosts morale and shows respect. This has a positive feedback loop for the ecosystem, as people will speak more positively about the project, ultimately bringing more people into it.

Direct communication with validators is also crucial, as they're the only other party other than the miners (and SN team) who can determine the success of the subnet. As it's been stated, you can't go to these conversations with hopes and dreams every time, and need an actual product (which is being developed as we speak). You also don't want to be a subnet that is all talk and delivers on nothing.

This subnet has certainly had its issues in the past, whether it be exploitation or poor scoring mechanics, but it's the best it's been now. That being said, there's still a lot of progress to be made. It's been nearly 4 months and it still feels like we're at the minimum viable stage of the subnet. Keep in mind that in reality, 4 months is nothing. The problem, however, is perception is more important than reality here. The continuous drop in emissions and lack of Discord communication (for the most part, with the exception of Rapido) ruins the confidence of miners. This results in subnet quality degradation. The other side, however, is as soon as emissions go back up again, the miners will be all happy again.

These are main points I feel this subnet needs to address:

- Continue/finish developing functionality for validators, as they determine if this subnet survives or not. Obviously, the sooner 1.4.0 and the frontend come out, the better
- Communicate updates/have a presence in the Discord more frequently. Dev updates have been managed well by Rapido. Seeing other NI team members being more active in the Discord would be nice
- Establish a larger social media/advertising presence. This will be critical for when Dynamic TAO is released, as the market will determine which subnets succeed. We don't want to play catch up at that time, as it'll probably be too late

The big challenge we're facing is how soon we can provide more value to the network and how quickly we can have validators recognize this. If it takes too long, we certainly may be deregistered prior to reaching the subnet's full potential. New subnets have been gaining a lot of attention. With how competitive it's getting, it's critical to provide/show value or risk becoming irrelevant. In the meantime, I'm all for a boost in communication/presence in the Discord from NI team members. It shouldn't take away from any development efforts and if it does, the team is short on staff.
